Steps to Solve:

1. Test for Prototype Pollution

Try the common prototype pollution payloads:
/?__proto__.foo=bar
/?__proto__[foo]=bar
/?constructor.prototype.foo=bar

Open DevTools → Console and execute:
Object.prototype

Observe that the foo property is not added.

---

2. Bypass the Key Sanitization

Inspect the JavaScript files.

Notice that deparamSanitized.js sanitizes dangerous keys using sanitizeKey() from searchLoggerFiltered.js.

The filter only sanitizes keys once and does not sanitize recursively.

Bypass the filter using an obfuscated prototype pollution payload:
/?__pro__proto__to__[foo]=bar

Verify the pollution:
Object.prototype

The foo property is now added successfully.

---

3. Identify the Gadget

Inspect searchLogger.js.

Notice that if config.transport_url exists, it is assigned to:
script.src = config.transport_url;

Since transport_url is not defined by default, it can be inherited from Object.prototype.

---

4. Confirm the Gadget

Inject:
/?__pro__proto__to__[transport_url]=foo

Open DevTools → Elements.

Verify that the application creates:
<script src="foo"></script>

---

5. Trigger DOM XSS

Replace the payload with:
/?__pro__proto__to__[transport_url]=data:,alert(1);

The browser loads:
<script src="data:,alert(1);"></script>

alert(1) is executed and the lab is solved.
